author: brane
msg: Fix compiler error on Windows.
* svnadmin/main.c (create_stdio_stream): APR_DECLARE the open_fn
callback. This macro is not a no-op on Windows, and without this change,
the compiler complains about different function attributes (probably has
to do with the calling convention).

author: rooneg
msg: * subversion/clients/cmdline/util.c
(svn_cl__parse_all_args, svn_cl__parse_num_args): don't call
svn_cl__subcommand_help when we run into a problem, since we are about to
return an error which will cause the same function to be called further up
the chain anyway, which was resulting in us printing out the usage message
twice whenever this function failed.

author: cmpilato
msg: Complete (with time consumption caveats) issue #690: "svn log" should print
changed paths.
* subversion/libsvn_fs/fs.h
(svn_fs__revision_t): Fix typo.
* subversion/svnlook/main.c
(main): Changed initialization of context-bearing structure.
* subversion/libsvn_repos/log.c
(svn_repos_get_logs): Turn on the changed-path detection code again.
(detect_changed): Fix this to actually use the changed node's path,
not that of its parent directory.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/log-cmd.c
(log_message_receiver): Sort the changed_paths hash that get returned.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/props.c
(svn_ra_dav__get_baseline_info): Fix error string (no more "inrepository").
